<subSubSection id="91EB650BFF99FFA7FFEDB253FE9AFD52" pageId="16" pageNumber="167" type="description">
<paragraph id="D94E3680FF99FFA7FFEDB253FE9AFD52" blockId="16.[110,649,527,1699]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis id="EB85EA92FF99FFA7FFEDB253FE9AFD52" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Rhizome erect, stipes in whorls; rhizome scales narrowly lanceolate, light brown, sometimes with brown to black central stripe. Sterile lamina pinnatisect, with middle segments decurrent on rachis and lowest segments abruptly reduced to auricles; fertile lamina pinnate, with much reduced pinnae. Sori extending along most of fertile pinnae; indusium entire.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
